reviews.text: Good selection of dishes which were tasty and portions were pretty generous too. Conveniently located within Jem, can see why this place is always usually full as well.  Good amount of seats with a pretty quick turnover, and probably a more economical option within Jem (depending on the chosen dishes)
Mee rebus was extremely yummy & we had added bergedil. Service staff can be a little too fierce (especially towards non-locals) but otherwise, they are pretty fast and efficient.

16/1/24, New Year try the nasi Lemak still as good as before .

Today pack 2 x Nasi Lemak - just as warm and good as eating at the shop.

Best Nasi Lemak, have lunch twice a month - Nasi Padang is excellent too. They branches in IMM WOODLAND and PAYA LEBAR.

May 3, after doing the election vote decided to have Nasi Lemak, very good. Coffee is good. Everything is good. We recommend this place for spicy food.
